annotationA: Adaptor protein complex AP-3 small chain sigma3; Protein transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: lysosome organization; ommochrome biosynthetic process; eye pigment biosynthetic process; vesicle coating; synaptic vesicle coating; compound eye pigmentation; vesicle-mediated transport; intracellular transport; intracellular protein transport; neurotransmitter secretion
annotationB: Adaptor Protein complex 2, mu subunit is a component of the AP-2 adaptor complex, which recruits certain transmembrane proteins into clathrin-coated pits for endocytic internalization
